text: Zanele kaMagwaza-Msibi (1 February 1962 - 6 September 2021) was a South African politician. She was born in Makhosini, South Africa. In 2011, she was elected Leader of the National Freedom Party. From 2014 until 2019, she was a member of the National Assembly. In November 2014, kaMagwaza-Msibi was hospitalized in critical condition after having a stroke. She died on 6 September 2021 at a hospital in Durban, South Africa from COVID-19 at the age of 59.National Freedom Party leader Zanele kaMagwaza-Msibi dies ==References== Category:South African mayors Category:2021 deaths Category:1962 births Category:Deaths from the COVID-19 pandemic in Durban
